<p><strong>Guidance:</strong></p>
<p>
  The report should present when, where and how the Public Consultation was
  undertaken (Article 19(2 d)). In addition, it should explain whether the
  Public Consultation included all measures reported under Article 13, all
  exceptions reported under Article 14 and all ad-hoc measures under Article
  14(1), 14(3). If not, the report should provide a list of the measures and/or
  exceptions which were not included and a reason for this.
</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p>The assessor should check if:</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>The PoM clearly mentions the dates of the public consultation.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      The means of conducting the public consultation are clearly presented.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      The public consultation included all aspects of the PoM (All measures, All
      exceptions, Ad-hoc measures to continue pursuing the targets and prevent
      further deterioration).
    </p>
  </li>
  <li></li>
  <li>
    <p>
      For the response option, the assessors should select: &ldquo;Yes&rdquo; if
      all the information on public consultation (including dates of the public
      consultation, means of the public consultation, and the measures included
      in the public consultation) is presented, &ldquo;Partially&rdquo; if some
      of the information (one or two of the above information) is presented, and
      &ldquo;No&rdquo; if no information on public consultation was presented.
    </p>
  </li>
</ul>
